    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-28T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="737"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1066</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-28T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 29, 2 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1484. Department’s 1222, June 13, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d737fn1">Not
                        printed.</note>
                    <persName>Alfred G. Smith</persName>, accompanied by Capt. <persName>W. H.
                        Ellis</persName>, arrived Madrid, this morning.</p>
                <p>British Embassy, under date of 22d instant, informed this Embassy as follows:
                        “<persName>Carlton Levick</persName> of the Ministry of Shipping is leaving
                    for Madrid today in order to act as adviser on behalf of His Majesty’s
                    Government in these negotiations and he is further directed to act as adviser to
                    His Majesty’s Embassy in the same manner as <persName>Smith</persName> to
                    yourself.” <persName>Levick</persName> has arrived in Madrid. Negotiations,
                    under article 13, Spanish-American agreement, March 7, 1918, will be initiated
                    so soon as <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>
                    who has been ill past week has recovered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
